that you do not pull the rope.

76
00:06:09.077 --> 00:06:10.411
You never listen to anything.

77
00:06:11.037 --> 00:06:12.080
[scoffs]

78
00:06:12.914 --> 00:06:14.082
You purged it?

79
00:06:14.582 --> 00:06:15.833
The pond spirit?

80
00:06:17.960 --> 00:06:20.254
All I could do was make it weak for now.

81
00:06:21.631 --> 00:06:24.050
For a while. at least.
it will not be able to move.

82
00:06:34.977 --> 00:06:35.937
What's that look for?

83
00:06:36.020 --> 00:06:36.979
Iâ€¦

84
00:06:38.439 --> 00:06:42.693
I just regret misjudging your abilities.
and I took you for aâ€¦ layabout.

85
00:06:42.777 --> 00:06:44.070
[Gu-cheon scoffs]

86
00:06:44.153 --> 00:06:46.864
I thought you were irredeemable
and only cared about your own pleasure

87
00:06:46.948 --> 00:06:50.118
and were someone who had no respect
for other humans. other than.

88
00:06:51.577 --> 00:06:52.995
well. himself.

89
00:06:55.456 --> 00:06:57.333
-[clears throat]
-I mean. you're not wrong.

90
00:06:57.417 --> 00:07:00.628
But still. that does not
sit particularly right with me.

91
00:07:01.504 --> 00:07:07.552
His Majestyâ€¦ is going to thank you
for what you did to save Prince Yeongan.

92
00:07:08.177 --> 00:07:11.514
Then put in a good word with your father
so I may leave. will you?

93
00:07:12.640 --> 00:07:14.642
[pensive music playing]

94
00:07:16.727 --> 00:07:18.312
How do you know about that?

95
00:07:19.730 --> 00:07:22.233
-How long have you known?
-From the moment I saw you.

96
00:07:23.651 --> 00:07:26.988
Well. I wondered who His Majesty
would send to help in secret.

97
00:07:27.071 --> 00:07:29.282
And there you were.
with such delicate hands for a woman.

98
00:07:29.866 --> 00:07:32.493
[grunts. pants] Are you all right?

99
00:07:34.328 --> 00:07:36.873
Not to mention.
you are a spitting image of the man.

100
00:07:36.956 --> 00:07:37.999
Huh?

101
00:07:38.082 --> 00:07:39.000
You're strong-willed.

102
00:07:39.917 --> 00:07:43.379
And yourâ€¦ yourâ€¦ your stubborn look
says it all.

103
00:07:44.797 --> 00:07:47.592
Wait. is that why
you told me to show my blood?

104
00:07:48.843 --> 00:07:51.679
The royal bloodline
is why the spirit held a grudge.

105
00:07:51.762 --> 00:07:52.930
You used me as bait?

106
00:07:53.014 --> 00:07:56.350
The blood was used for a way to draw
the pond spirit's attention elsewhere.

107
00:07:56.434 --> 00:07:59.270
I can see now
that His Majesty chose the right person.

108
00:08:07.653 --> 00:08:09.197
And speaking of thatâ€¦

109
00:08:15.870 --> 00:08:18.581
Let's help each other.
without His Majesty's knowing about it.

110
00:08:19.165 --> 00:08:20.166
[scoffs]

111
00:08:21.209 --> 00:08:22.126
[sighs]

112
00:08:23.294 --> 00:08:24.212
[Gu-cheon] Here.

113
00:08:29.717 --> 00:08:33.346
The truth is. I'm allowed
to stay here under close supervision

114
00:08:33.846 --> 00:08:35.556
while the spirit is being dealt with.

115
00:08:36.641 --> 00:08:37.600
So.

116
00:08:38.518 --> 00:08:41.020
buy me time
to stay here a little bit longer.

117
00:08:42.730 --> 00:08:44.690
And what exactly do you plan to do?

118
00:08:45.399 --> 00:08:46.943
I am going to kill someone

119
00:08:47.527 --> 00:08:48.903
here in the palace.

120
00:08:49.904 --> 00:08:50.905
[man] <i>Your Majesty.</i>

121
00:08:51.489 --> 00:08:54.492
A child who once served
the late Crown Prince

122
00:08:55.076 --> 00:08:57.245
has requested an audience with you.

123
00:09:01.123 --> 00:09:04.168
He claims to know about the spirit

124
00:09:05.253 --> 00:09:07.171
and the Crown Prince.

125
00:09:07.672 --> 00:09:09.674
[suspenseful music playing]

126
00:09:11.300 --> 00:09:12.552
He can enter.

127
00:09:24.063 --> 00:09:25.022
[door closes]

128
00:09:26.899 --> 00:09:28.234
[King] All right.

129
00:09:28.317 --> 00:09:29.735
So then.

130
00:09:31.404 --> 00:09:32.989
do you have something to say?

131
00:09:33.614 --> 00:09:35.616
[breathing shakily]

132
00:09:56.762 --> 00:09:58.764
[breathing nervously]

133
00:10:01.434 --> 00:10:03.060
[nervous breathing echoes]

134
00:10:07.106 --> 00:10:08.649
You are still young.

135
00:10:10.568 --> 00:10:12.695
Yet you are quite courageous.

136
00:10:20.703 --> 00:10:22.121
[man] Yes. right here.

137
00:10:43.934 --> 00:10:45.311
[man grunts. gasps]

138
00:10:45.394 --> 00:10:47.396
[tense music playing]

139
00:10:48.731 --> 00:10:50.691
[grunting]

140
00:10:51.192 --> 00:10:54.403
[Gu-cheon] <i>Why should I become your ally</i>
<i>without His Majesty's knowledge?</i>

141
00:10:54.904 --> 00:10:57.198
Because those
who know the palace's secrets

142
00:10:57.281 --> 00:10:59.575
are not permitted
to leave this place alive.

143
00:11:00.576 --> 00:11:02.411
So if I help you with your task.

144
00:11:02.495 --> 00:11:04.872
you will let me leave
the palace alive after I do?

145
00:11:06.957 --> 00:11:08.084
[Saeng-gang] Hmmâ€¦

146
00:11:11.587 --> 00:11:12.630
[Saeng-gang sighs]

147
00:11:17.551 --> 00:11:18.678
[groans]

148
00:11:28.938 --> 00:11:31.065
The bell though. How did you hear it?

149
00:11:34.568 --> 00:11:37.738
I have a gift as well.
It's rather similar to your own.

150
00:11:38.239 --> 00:11:40.241
[bell jingles]

151
00:11:40.324 --> 00:11:42.326
[ominous ethereal music playing]

152
00:12:06.726 --> 00:12:08.686
[bell jingles in distance]

153
00:12:12.231 --> 00:12:14.400
-[spectral shriek]
-[child gasps] Mother!

154
00:12:14.483 --> 00:12:16.485
[woman gasps] Are you all right?

155
00:12:17.820 --> 00:12:19.655
Did you see something inside?

156
00:12:20.364 --> 00:12:22.199
-Oh my.
-[door opens]

157
00:12:22.283 --> 00:12:24.660
[Jang] And what do you think
you two are doing here?

158
00:12:26.328 --> 00:12:27.705
[Saeng-gang] <i>"The pond spirit."</i>

159
00:12:28.706 --> 00:12:31.792
<i>"The serpent's shed skin</i>
<i>killed the dragon's child."</i>

160
00:12:32.501 --> 00:12:34.503
Those were the words
that were spoken by a spirit

161
00:12:34.587 --> 00:12:36.589
once trapped there
when I was a young girl.

162
00:12:36.672 --> 00:12:39.008
The dragon's child refers
to the King's son.

163
00:12:39.091 --> 00:12:42.970
And the shed skin of the serpent
is the pond spirit. I would gather.

164
00:12:43.554 --> 00:12:44.513
What are you on about?

165
00:12:44.597 --> 00:12:46.015
If we look into the salt storehouse.

166
00:12:46.098 --> 00:12:48.309
we can learn information
surrounding the spirit.

167
00:12:51.937 --> 00:12:54.565
-Don't tell me that the reason--
-That's not yours to worry about.

168
00:12:57.818 --> 00:13:01.197
For now.
you must investigate the pond spirit.

169
00:13:01.280 --> 00:13:05.493
So anyway. you were cast out of the palace
for hearing ghosts. huh?

170
00:13:05.576 --> 00:13:09.663
Even though you're a princess.
you have the gifts of a shaman.

171
00:13:10.247 --> 00:13:13.584
What happened when you were young
that led you to hear voices?

172
00:13:13.667 --> 00:13:15.669
How did you grow up
that you dig into people's hearts

173
00:13:15.753 --> 00:13:17.838
with every word you seem to say?

174
00:13:19.673 --> 00:13:22.468
Wow. you're getting all worked up
over nothing.

175
00:13:22.551 --> 00:13:23.552
Nothing?

176
00:13:25.054 --> 00:13:26.138
[Saeng-gang scoffs]

177
00:13:27.097 --> 00:13:30.142
You truly do not know how
to consider other people's feelings.

178
00:13:30.226 --> 00:13:32.478
You must be disliked
by your friends and family.

179
00:13:32.561 --> 00:13:35.147
I have neither to speak of. I'm an orphan.

180
00:13:35.231 --> 00:13:36.065
[Saeng-gang] Oh.

181
00:13:38.150 --> 00:13:39.819
And you are one to talk.

182
00:13:40.319 --> 00:13:42.321
Do you have any friends? Huh?

183
00:13:42.404 --> 00:13:43.447
[Saeng-gang scoffs]

184
00:13:43.948 --> 00:13:45.699
Are all royalty born annoying.
because maybe--

185
00:13:45.783 --> 00:13:46.951
That is enough!

186
00:13:48.077 --> 00:13:50.704
You must hurry up
and investigate the salt storehouse.

187
00:13:50.788 --> 00:13:52.206
[sighs]

188
00:13:53.290 --> 00:13:54.375
[Gu-cheon scoffs]

189
00:13:54.875 --> 00:13:58.379
Seriously. this pond spiritâ€¦ [sighs]

190
00:13:59.630 --> 00:14:01.215
-Hold on.
-[groans]

191
00:14:04.301 --> 00:14:05.678
[Gu-cheon] Don't tell meâ€¦

192
00:14:05.761 --> 00:14:07.763
[suspenseful music playing]

193
00:14:10.099 --> 00:14:11.183
[sighs]

194
00:14:12.768 --> 00:14:13.978
[Gu-cheon] Ohâ€¦

195
00:14:14.061 --> 00:14:15.187
Can it be?

196
00:14:15.688 --> 00:14:17.690
[Saeng-gang]
Why are you going there? What is it?

197
00:14:17.773 --> 00:14:19.316
-[Gu-cheon] No way.
-Whatâ€¦

198
00:14:19.817 --> 00:14:22.027
-[Gu-cheon] Wait.
-Is there something there?

199
00:14:22.111 --> 00:14:23.320
[Gu-cheon sighs]

200
00:14:24.572 --> 00:14:25.656
[Gu-cheon grunts]

201
00:14:27.658 --> 00:14:29.660
I was saving this for later.

202
00:14:29.743 --> 00:14:30.661
[creature snarls]

203
00:14:31.287 --> 00:14:32.788
[Gu-cheon grunts. gasps]

204
00:14:32.872 --> 00:14:34.874
-What are you doing?
-It really is here. [pants]

205
00:14:34.957 --> 00:14:36.250
-A gwi-mae.
-It is?

206
00:14:36.333 --> 00:14:37.793
I need to figure out what kind it is.

207
00:14:39.628 --> 00:14:41.088
Where did you get the rice cake from?

208
00:14:41.672 --> 00:14:43.007
-Wait. why are you throwing--
-Sh!

209
00:14:44.258 --> 00:14:46.468
[softly] Keep it down for a moment. Huh?

210
00:14:51.765 --> 00:14:53.642
[creature purrs]

211
00:14:53.726 --> 00:14:54.560
[gasps]

212
00:14:58.355 --> 00:15:00.774
-[coos]
-[Gu-cheon] This can't be happening.

213
00:15:00.858 --> 00:15:02.985
-No.
-[Saeng-gang] What do you see?

214
00:15:03.068 --> 00:15:05.070
[whimsical music playing]

215
00:15:06.447 --> 00:15:08.365
-[Saeng-gang] Heyâ€¦
-We need to go immediately.

216
00:15:09.450 --> 00:15:10.367
Follow me.

217
00:15:11.493 --> 00:15:12.328
Come on!

218
00:15:12.411 --> 00:15:15.122
[Saeng-gang] Butâ€¦ we need to checkâ€¦

219
00:15:15.205 --> 00:15:17.207
[footsteps pattering]

220
00:15:18.584 --> 00:15:20.586
[growls. swallows]

221
00:15:22.129 --> 00:15:23.422
[both panting]

222
00:15:23.505 --> 00:15:26.884
You said it was a gwi-mae.
and that it is bound to one place.

223
00:15:27.426 --> 00:15:28.802
-We should be fine.
-Hang on.

224
00:15:28.886 --> 00:15:29.887
Justâ€¦ wait a minute!

225
00:15:29.970 --> 00:15:30.888
[gasps]

226
00:15:32.514 --> 00:15:35.225
That oneâ€¦ is a special one.

227
00:15:35.309 --> 00:15:36.810
It's called a ggeomeoksali.

228
00:15:36.894 --> 00:15:39.813
It latches onto the living. not a place.
and drains their yang energy.

229
00:15:39.897 --> 00:15:41.899
-And those who have been affected by itâ€¦
-Their yangâ€¦

230
00:15:42.399 --> 00:15:44.234
â€¦will die after witnessing terror.

231
00:15:45.861 --> 00:15:47.446
A truly terrifying creature.

232
00:15:47.529 --> 00:15:48.948
Butâ€¦ [gasps]

233
00:15:49.823 --> 00:15:53.035
[sighs] I understand.
so stop pushing. Wait.

234
00:15:54.286 --> 00:15:56.372
Let me show you where you will be staying.

235
00:15:56.455 --> 00:15:59.583
His Majesty had your quarters changed
because you saved Prince Yeongan.

236
00:16:00.626 --> 00:16:02.628
Why are you telling me this now?

237
00:16:03.379 --> 00:16:05.130
-Wellâ€¦
-Where is it?

238
00:16:07.549 --> 00:16:09.134
Over there. That way.

239
00:16:10.260 --> 00:16:11.553
-[Gu-cheon] Quickly.
-[grunts]

240
00:16:11.637 --> 00:16:14.640
-[Gu-cheon] Come on.
-I am going. I am! [grunts]

241
00:16:18.018 --> 00:16:19.520
[Gu-cheon] Good grief.

242
00:16:19.603 --> 00:16:21.689
This is truly unbelievable.

243
00:16:23.273 --> 00:16:24.316
Goodness.

244
00:16:24.400 --> 00:16:25.859
[Saeng-gang] What are you staring at?

245
00:16:25.943 --> 00:16:29.196
[Gu-cheon] I was a fool to trust him.
My goodness. seriously. Ugh.

246
00:16:29.279 --> 00:16:31.657
So. more comfortable lodging?

247
00:16:33.158 --> 00:16:34.076
[sighs]

248
00:16:35.744 --> 00:16:38.038
[Gu-cheon] It's just the room
across from the previous one.

249
00:16:38.122 --> 00:16:40.541
-[whimsical music playing]
-[Gu-cheon sighs]

250
00:16:43.544 --> 00:16:44.461
Oh.

251
00:16:44.545 --> 00:16:45.963
It followed us all the way here.

252
00:16:50.259 --> 00:16:52.469
-The ggeomeoksali.
-What?

253
00:16:54.096 --> 00:16:55.264
Ggeomeoksali.

254
00:16:59.560 --> 00:17:01.061
-[coos]
-[Gu-cheon] No.

255
00:17:02.604 --> 00:17:04.898
That bastard is as clingy
as sticky rice cakes.

256
00:17:04.982 --> 00:17:06.525
[music fades]

257
00:17:07.526 --> 00:17:09.278
[Saeng-gang]
What has made you act like that?

258
00:17:12.990 --> 00:17:15.200
There is nothing here. [sighs]

259
00:17:19.538 --> 00:17:20.372
[clears throat]

260
00:17:22.374 --> 00:17:23.333
Anywayâ€¦

261
00:17:25.377 --> 00:17:28.213
Looks as if His Majesty is pleased
with how you handled it.

262
00:17:28.881 --> 00:17:30.049
That is a relief.

263
00:17:30.132 --> 00:17:31.759
But just temporary.

264
00:17:32.634 --> 00:17:34.678
If the pond spirit shows itself again.

265
00:17:35.429 --> 00:17:37.598
it is certain
that Prince Yeongan will soon die.

266
00:17:37.681 --> 00:17:39.683
-[gong plays]
-[shaman chanting]

267
00:17:40.350 --> 00:17:42.352
[groaning]

268
00:17:43.645 --> 00:17:45.856
[woman] You must stay strong.
Prince Yeongan.

269
00:17:48.067 --> 00:17:49.026
Give it to me.

270
00:17:51.278 --> 00:17:52.946
Please come back to us.

271
00:17:54.031 --> 00:17:56.033
[chanting continues]

272
00:17:58.494 --> 00:18:00.496
[music intensifies]

273
00:18:02.623 --> 00:18:05.709
[man 1] Your Majesty.
now that even the last remaining prince.

274
00:18:05.793 --> 00:18:07.336
Yeongan. lies so ill.

275
00:18:07.419 --> 00:18:10.464
the succession of this realm
is gravely imperiled.

276
00:18:10.547 --> 00:18:13.258
[man 2] Rumors surrounding
the East Palace continue to circulate.

277
00:18:13.342 --> 00:18:15.844
shaking the very foundations
of the nation.

278
00:18:15.928 --> 00:18:19.223
[Queen] The nation's foundations
are shaken. you say?

279
00:18:19.306 --> 00:18:21.475
You should mind the words you choose.

280
00:18:21.558 --> 00:18:23.477
So long as I draw breath.

281
00:18:23.977 --> 00:18:27.648
this great nation's foundations
will not be shaken.

282
00:18:28.482 --> 00:18:31.944
[Jang] Your Majesty.
Prince Iksang has arrived.

283
00:18:34.279 --> 00:18:35.948
[man 3] Prince Iksang?
What's he doing here?

284
00:18:36.031 --> 00:18:37.574
Greetings. my friends.

285
00:18:37.658 --> 00:18:39.576
Have you had your meal today?

286
00:18:39.660 --> 00:18:41.161
[laughs]

287
00:18:42.621 --> 00:18:44.957
You are looking younger than ever. Aunt.

288
00:18:46.583 --> 00:18:50.254
I see you still prefer to address me so.
Prince Iksang.

289
00:18:51.463 --> 00:18:53.382
How have you fared as of late?

290
00:18:53.465 --> 00:18:56.051
I have returned from a tiger hunt
in Hobyeong Valley.

291
00:18:56.135 --> 00:18:58.178
I also lingered
at the Nine Valleys of Hwayang.

292
00:18:58.262 --> 00:18:59.721
indulging in idle pleasures.

293
00:18:59.805 --> 00:19:00.806
[chuckles]

294
00:19:00.889 --> 00:19:02.182
If I may say so.

295
00:19:02.266 --> 00:19:04.935
you should not remain confined
to the palace walls.

296
00:19:05.018 --> 00:19:07.062
A period of rest outside is deserved.

297
00:19:07.646 --> 00:19:09.231
I am not sure.

298
00:19:10.357 --> 00:19:13.110
I entered these walls
as Crown Princess at age 11.

299
00:19:13.193 --> 00:19:15.904
I have never once set foot
beyond its gates.

300
00:19:16.780 --> 00:19:20.492
This palace is where I shall stay
until the day I die.

301
00:19:22.327 --> 00:19:23.871
You remain unchanged.

302
00:19:23.954 --> 00:19:26.123
So why did you wish to see me again?

303
00:19:31.170 --> 00:19:33.088
And how is your son?

304
00:19:36.800 --> 00:19:38.927
[intriguing pensive music playing]

305
00:19:42.848 --> 00:19:44.766
He is doing well.

306
00:19:46.685 --> 00:19:49.980
Unlike his father.
he delights in scholarly pursuits.

307
00:19:50.063 --> 00:19:53.901
Even so.
a collateral figure of the royal family

308
00:19:53.984 --> 00:19:55.485
is barred from holding office.

309
00:19:56.153 --> 00:19:59.156
A small stream
cut off from the main current

310
00:19:59.865 --> 00:20:02.034
cannot easily spread.

311
00:20:02.117 --> 00:20:07.372
However. should that main river grow foul
and become dryâ€¦

312
00:20:10.667 --> 00:20:14.671
it should be cut away.
making a new channel flow in place of it.

313
00:20:16.048 --> 00:20:19.092
How dare a feng shui master like you
venture to seek out an audience

314
00:20:19.176 --> 00:20:21.345
with Her Majesty so lightly!

315
00:20:21.428 --> 00:20:22.512
Get out at once.

316
00:20:22.596 --> 00:20:25.599
He entered the palace
under His Majesty's command.

317
00:20:25.682 --> 00:20:28.185
He promptly arrived
with important information

318
00:20:29.561 --> 00:20:31.188
and at the will of His Majesty.

319
00:20:33.065 --> 00:20:34.233
Wait here.

320
00:20:42.074 --> 00:20:44.493
She sure is damn prickly. that woman.

321
00:20:46.954 --> 00:20:49.498
She stands above
all the ladies of the palace.

322
00:20:49.581 --> 00:20:51.875
You suppose
an audience with her comes easy?

323
00:20:52.459 --> 00:20:54.461
[hissing]

324
00:20:56.463 --> 00:20:58.465
[unsettling music playing]

325
00:21:00.467 --> 00:21:01.885
I hear a noise coming close.

326
00:21:01.969 --> 00:21:03.971
[hissing continues]

327
00:21:05.472 --> 00:21:07.474
[music intensifies]

328
00:21:19.152 --> 00:21:21.613
-This place is crawling with yin.
-[bell jingling]

329
00:21:28.662 --> 00:21:30.664
[sinister hissing]

330
00:21:32.833 --> 00:21:34.293
[door opens]

331
00:21:35.711 --> 00:21:36.795
[door closes]

332
00:21:39.423 --> 00:21:40.924
Her Majesty is still unavailable.

333
00:21:41.008 --> 00:21:42.592
You should leave.

334
00:21:46.179 --> 00:21:47.806
[Gu-cheon] Oh.
what a mighty shame that is.

335
00:21:47.889 --> 00:21:51.727
You see. I had something to tell her
about the pond spirit.

336
00:21:51.810 --> 00:21:54.438
Pardon? The pond spirit. you say?

337
00:21:56.857 --> 00:21:59.026
Then please convey this one message.

338
00:22:02.154 --> 00:22:04.531
Tell her she should start to think about

339
00:22:04.614 --> 00:22:07.409
who might rule next
once the Crown Prince is dead.

340
00:22:07.993 --> 00:22:08.827
[Jang] What?

341
00:22:09.619 --> 00:22:10.704
Who might be next?

342
00:22:16.001 --> 00:22:17.419
What does he mean?

343
00:22:25.010 --> 00:22:26.928
It was a waste to come here.

344
00:22:28.764 --> 00:22:30.390
Trying to meet with the Queen Dowager.

345
00:22:30.474 --> 00:22:32.559
No. there was a gain.

346
00:22:32.642 --> 00:22:34.186
[Saeng-gang] A gain? What do you mean?

347
00:22:35.604 --> 00:22:37.147
Oh. Are youâ€¦

348
00:22:41.401 --> 00:22:42.694
[music fades]

349
00:22:43.320 --> 00:22:45.530
[breathing nervously]

350
00:22:46.782 --> 00:22:48.784
She lives in a residence that's private.

351
00:22:49.368 --> 00:22:51.036
Why is she in the palace wandering?

352
00:22:54.623 --> 00:22:55.832
Who was that?

353
00:22:55.916 --> 00:22:57.042
You know each other?

354
00:22:57.125 --> 00:22:59.252
She is my grandmother.

355
00:22:59.336 --> 00:23:01.213
The birth mother of His Majesty.

356
00:23:02.464 --> 00:23:04.466
[mysterious ethereal music playing]

357
00:23:06.676 --> 00:23:08.637
Is that why relations
between the Queen Dowager

358
00:23:08.720 --> 00:23:09.805
and the King are strained?

359
00:23:10.514 --> 00:23:11.765
They're not blood-related?

360
00:23:14.059 --> 00:23:15.102
Or rather.

361
00:23:16.186 --> 00:23:18.438
because the King
was the child of a concubine.

362
00:23:21.817 --> 00:23:23.193
<i>Thirty years ago.</i>

363
00:23:24.194 --> 00:23:28.907
<i>all of His Majesty's brothers died</i>
<i>for reasons that were never made clear.</i>

364
00:23:31.034 --> 00:23:33.620
<i>He alone survived among</i>
<i>the late King's sons</i>

365
00:23:33.703 --> 00:23:34.955
<i>and was named Crown Prince.</i>

366
00:23:35.038 --> 00:23:37.207
<i>but because the lowborn blood</i>
<i>of a court lady</i>

367
00:23:37.290 --> 00:23:39.084
<i>was said to run in his veins.</i>

368
00:23:39.167 --> 00:23:41.962
<i>he was never fully acknowledged</i>
<i>as the Crown Prince.</i>

369
00:23:42.462 --> 00:23:45.298
<i>Not even now.</i>
<i>after he ascended to the throne.</i>

370
00:23:57.561 --> 00:23:59.104
[man] Your Majesty.

371
00:23:59.187 --> 00:24:01.481
for the sake of this country
and its people.

372
00:24:01.565 --> 00:24:04.192
a new Crown Prince must be appointed.

373
00:24:04.276 --> 00:24:05.861
This. I am aware of.

374
00:24:06.361 --> 00:24:10.824
However. Prince Yeongan's health
has yet to fully recover.

375
00:24:10.907 --> 00:24:14.035
That is precisely why
we are mentioning this. Your Majesty.

376
00:24:14.119 --> 00:24:16.037
It is imperative that measures be taken.

377
00:24:17.831 --> 00:24:19.583
What kind of measures?

378
00:24:19.666 --> 00:24:22.502
[man 2] You must move forth
and select one of the royal kin

379
00:24:22.586 --> 00:24:25.255
and name him your new Crown Prince.
Your Majesty.

380
00:24:26.131 --> 00:24:28.133
[man 1] Grant your royal assent.

381
00:24:28.800 --> 00:24:31.303
[all] Grant your royal assent.

382
00:24:34.097 --> 00:24:37.225
Do all of you believe the same thing?

383
00:24:39.019 --> 00:24:40.520
That death will soon take my son?

384
00:24:40.604 --> 00:24:42.105
-[all exclaim]
-Uhâ€¦

385
00:24:42.189 --> 00:24:44.649
How could we harbor such irreverence?

386
00:24:44.733 --> 00:24:46.651
That is not what we imply or intend.
Your Majesty.

387
00:24:46.735 --> 00:24:48.153
That is not what you imply?!

388
00:24:48.236 --> 00:24:50.280
[tense music playing]

389
00:24:50.363 --> 00:24:52.282
Then whose intention is it?

390
00:24:55.827 --> 00:24:57.996
Is it the Queen Dowager's intention?

391
00:25:01.374 --> 00:25:04.211
[Iksang] I am deeply disappointed in you.

392
00:25:05.462 --> 00:25:08.215
I went above and beyond
to get you in here.

393
00:25:08.298 --> 00:25:12.302
yet you failed to command a single spirit
and. instead. restored his health.

394
00:25:13.303 --> 00:25:15.931
I did not drive away the spirit.

395
00:25:17.182 --> 00:25:20.060
I only sought to draw the spirit
toward the Prince.

396
00:25:20.143 --> 00:25:23.104
Then was there another
who drove the spirit away?

397
00:25:23.188 --> 00:25:25.941
The feng shui master the King brought in
is rather suspicious.

398
00:25:26.024 --> 00:25:29.069
The King? [chuckles]
He brought in a master of feng shui?

399
00:25:37.577 --> 00:25:40.038
I want you to keep him under close watch.

400
00:25:40.121 --> 00:25:43.667
If he truly is the one helping
to destroy spiritsâ€¦

401
00:25:46.002 --> 00:25:47.546
he will die at our hands.

402
00:25:48.171 --> 00:25:50.257
The more spirits run rampant
within the palace.

403
00:25:50.340 --> 00:25:52.300
the further the King
is driven into a corner.

404
00:25:52.884 --> 00:25:54.511
And that serves me well.

405
00:25:56.054 --> 00:25:58.848
Prince Iksang
was at the Queen Dowager's residence?

406
00:26:02.644 --> 00:26:05.438
My. that is truly impressive.

407
00:26:06.648 --> 00:26:08.650
[tense music continues]

408
00:26:09.526 --> 00:26:10.610
[scoffs]

409
00:26:13.738 --> 00:26:18.118
So she plans
to alter the royal bloodline after all?

410
00:26:19.661 --> 00:26:23.707
<i>She intends to sever the curse</i>
<i>that has endured for 30 years</i>

411
00:26:24.332 --> 00:26:26.126
<i>and begin anew.</i>

412
00:26:28.753 --> 00:26:30.922
<i>But it will not be so easy.</i>

413
00:26:34.593 --> 00:26:37.679
<i>And for someone who has been bound by sin.</i>

414
00:26:38.221 --> 00:26:41.141
<i>does she truly believe she can escape it?</i>

415
00:26:46.563 --> 00:26:48.315
[glass shattering]

416
00:26:53.236 --> 00:26:55.030
[glass shattering]

417
00:26:55.864 --> 00:26:57.449
[music fades]

418
00:26:57.532 --> 00:26:58.950
[spectral hiss]

419
00:27:13.923 --> 00:27:15.091
You all right?

420
00:27:16.384 --> 00:27:17.802
-You okay?
-[grunts]

421
00:27:17.886 --> 00:27:20.221
What's wrong with you? [gasps]

422
00:27:20.305 --> 00:27:23.350
[spectral screaming]

423
00:27:24.184 --> 00:27:25.769
Sorry. who are you?

424
00:27:25.852 --> 00:27:28.355
Ji-yul. a sanggaksi
serving in the Saenggwabang.

425
00:27:28.438 --> 00:27:31.024
I will be sharing this chamber with you
starting today.

426
00:27:31.107 --> 00:27:32.984
Huh? That cannot be possible.

427
00:27:33.068 --> 00:27:33.902
[Ji-yul] There.

428
00:27:34.819 --> 00:27:38.823
Umâ€¦ I was told
I would have my own quarters.

429
00:27:38.907 --> 00:27:41.368
-I have never shared a chamber.
-What's this?

430
00:27:41.451 --> 00:27:43.495
This must be
rather uncomfortable for you. so--

431
00:27:43.578 --> 00:27:44.871
Not at all.

432
00:27:45.372 --> 00:27:49.584
Before I entered the palace.
I shared a room with nine of my family.

433
00:27:49.668 --> 00:27:50.752
[chuckles]

434
00:27:51.711 --> 00:27:52.629
Ah.

435
00:27:52.712 --> 00:27:54.964
-[objects clattering]
-[indistinct chattering]

436
00:27:59.010 --> 00:28:01.096
What might all that fuss be about?

437
00:28:01.179 --> 00:28:03.973
What? Oh my. You haven't heard about it?

438
00:28:04.057 --> 00:28:06.685
A spirit was seen
at the Queen Dowager's quarters.

439
00:28:06.768 --> 00:28:07.852
A spirit. really?

440
00:28:07.936 --> 00:28:11.606
Yes. Ever since I entered the palace.
a lot of incidents have happened.

441
00:28:11.690 --> 00:28:13.650
I heard a spirit showed up
at the Saenggwabang too.

442
00:28:13.733 --> 00:28:14.567
Hang on.

443
00:28:15.068 --> 00:28:17.529
Tell me all that you have heard
about the spirits.

444
00:28:17.612 --> 00:28:20.573
[groans] Gosh. I'm so cold.

445
00:28:20.657 --> 00:28:21.783
[groans]

446
00:28:28.790 --> 00:28:30.458
[ggeomeoksali purrs]

447
00:28:30.542 --> 00:28:32.293
[screaming]

448
00:28:32.377 --> 00:28:34.379
[whimsical music playing]

449
00:28:36.423 --> 00:28:38.466
[grunts] Damn it! Jeez.

450
00:28:38.550 --> 00:28:40.343
[panting]

451
00:28:41.094 --> 00:28:41.928
What theâ€¦

452
00:28:42.595 --> 00:28:44.222
When did you get in here?

453
00:28:45.640 --> 00:28:47.517
Hey. Stop that.

454
00:28:48.893 --> 00:28:50.937
-Stop coming closer!
-[coos]

455
00:28:51.020 --> 00:28:52.522
Who said you could act all cute?

456
00:28:53.898 --> 00:28:56.735
Why? Why pick on me? Huh?

457
00:28:56.818 --> 00:28:57.986
-Why?
-[door opens]

458
00:28:59.446 --> 00:29:02.198
Apparently. a salt storehouse spirit
is in the Queen Dowager's quarters.

459
00:29:02.282 --> 00:29:03.491
[uneasy music playing]

460
00:29:03.575 --> 00:29:04.617
You mean right now?

461
00:29:04.701 --> 00:29:07.162
We must go.
We need to investigate immediately.

462
00:29:07.829 --> 00:29:10.290
Sure. I cannot wait to get out of here.

463
00:29:10.915 --> 00:29:12.167
[Saeng-gang] What?

464
00:29:15.962 --> 00:29:17.046
[sighs]

465
00:29:20.633 --> 00:29:22.635
[uneasy music continues]

466
00:29:31.227 --> 00:29:33.646
[spectral murmuring]

467
00:29:33.730 --> 00:29:34.564
[gasps]

468
00:29:35.774 --> 00:29:36.775
What is it?

469
00:29:38.359 --> 00:29:39.778
Do you hear something?

470
00:29:41.237 --> 00:29:43.323
I can't make it out.
It's too subtle for me to hear.

471
00:29:43.406 --> 00:29:44.991
Too faint to understand.

472
00:29:46.284 --> 00:29:47.327
[Gu-cheon] Hmm.

473
00:29:51.372 --> 00:29:53.416
I should step inside to hear better.

474
00:30:04.052 --> 00:30:05.845
Do you really have to go in alone?

475
00:30:11.518 --> 00:30:12.519
I will be fine.

476
00:30:13.019 --> 00:30:15.313
Okay. then I will wait out here for you.

477
00:30:25.406 --> 00:30:27.450
[wind whistles]

478
00:30:28.827 --> 00:30:30.119
[breathing nervously]

479
00:30:50.974 --> 00:30:52.976
-[spectral murmuring]
-[metallic clank]

480
00:30:54.853 --> 00:30:57.272
[breathing nervously]

481
00:31:05.405 --> 00:31:07.407
[spectral murmuring continues]

482
00:31:11.077 --> 00:31:12.704
Say what you need to say.

483
00:31:13.663 --> 00:31:15.957
Tell me what happened. Please say it.

484
00:31:17.000 --> 00:31:19.586
[spectral murmuring intensifies]

485
00:31:23.256 --> 00:31:25.216
[spectral screaming]

486
00:31:30.388 --> 00:31:32.056
[spectral streaming continues]

487
00:31:32.640 --> 00:31:34.642
[screaming subsides]

488
00:31:34.726 --> 00:31:36.728
[breathing shakily]

489
00:31:39.522 --> 00:31:41.357
[tense music stinger]

490
00:31:42.108 --> 00:31:45.695
[spirit] The serpent's shed skin
killed the dragon's child.

491
00:31:47.530 --> 00:31:51.117
[Jang] <i>"The serpent's shed skin</i>
<i>killed the dragon's child."</i>

492
00:31:51.743 --> 00:31:54.162
-Tell me who wrote these words.
-[women sobbing]

493
00:31:55.246 --> 00:31:58.958
The dragon's child refers
to the late Crown Prince.

494
00:31:59.792 --> 00:32:02.795
Her Majesty. the Queen.
was born in the Year of the Snake.

495
00:32:02.879 --> 00:32:06.049
So. that implies
that the Crown Prince died

496
00:32:06.132 --> 00:32:07.884
because of Her Majesty.

497
00:32:07.967 --> 00:32:12.472
It seems one of you wenches
has insulted Her Majesty's house.

498
00:32:14.265 --> 00:32:16.559
You will starve in here until you confess.

499
00:32:16.643 --> 00:32:19.270
Not even a drop of water will be given.

500
00:32:19.354 --> 00:32:21.356
[women crying]

501
00:32:24.359 --> 00:32:25.318
[door closes]

502
00:32:25.401 --> 00:32:27.403
[crying]

503
00:32:28.029 --> 00:32:30.031
[stirring melancholy music playing]

504
00:32:34.327 --> 00:32:36.329
[women screaming. crying]

505
00:32:38.915 --> 00:32:40.917
[screaming. crying continues]

506
00:33:01.479 --> 00:33:03.564
They burned to death whilst in there?

507
00:33:07.527 --> 00:33:10.613
Gather the court ladies' bones in jars
and bury the lot.

508
00:33:11.322 --> 00:33:14.909
Their vengeful spirits must be sealed
so they cannot harm the royal house.

509
00:33:14.993 --> 00:33:15.994
[Jang] Yes. Your Majesty.

510
00:33:16.077 --> 00:33:18.079
[shaman chanting]

511
00:33:31.843 --> 00:33:33.094
[music swells]

512
00:33:33.177 --> 00:33:34.679
-[music fades]
-[chanting stops]

513
00:33:34.762 --> 00:33:36.931
[Queen] Have you had the chance yet

514
00:33:37.015 --> 00:33:39.976
to look into who broke the sealed jars?

515
00:33:41.060 --> 00:33:42.645
I have looked into it.

516
00:33:43.146 --> 00:33:46.649
but I could not find the person
who entered the salt storehouse.

517
00:33:46.733 --> 00:33:48.860
-[unsettling music playing]
-[Jang exhales]

518
00:33:48.943 --> 00:33:51.195
This must have been done by someone

519
00:33:51.779 --> 00:33:54.157
who knows exactly what these jars are.

520
00:33:55.324 --> 00:33:58.536
But are we not the only ones in the palace
who know of those jars?

521
00:34:00.079 --> 00:34:03.875
This must be an aimed attack against me.
but who would do that?

522
00:34:06.753 --> 00:34:07.795
Yes.

523
00:34:08.880 --> 00:34:11.299
I know of a person who would do it.

524
00:34:11.799 --> 00:34:13.801
-[Jang] Who is it?
-[breathes angrily]

525
00:34:14.594 --> 00:34:18.723
I can see clearly how my fear of spirits
momentarily clouded my sight.

526
00:34:18.806 --> 00:34:20.975
Why did I not see it coming
sooner than this?

527
00:34:21.642 --> 00:34:24.729
<i>All of this trouble began</i>
<i>after I met with Prince Iksang.</i>

528
00:34:24.812 --> 00:34:27.774
[man] Prince Yeongan
has overcome the crisis. Your Majesty.

529
00:34:27.857 --> 00:34:31.527
Therefore. I believe now is the time
for you to appoint the Crown Prince.

530
00:34:31.611 --> 00:34:34.781
[Queen] <i>His Majesty</i>
<i>saw straight through my heart.</i>

531
00:34:34.864 --> 00:34:37.700
He is trying to stop me.
no matter the cost.

532
00:34:37.784 --> 00:34:40.620
I know that he means to oppose me
with wielding spirits.

533
00:34:40.703 --> 00:34:44.123
So if I'm right. it would seem
the King wants me dead tonight!

534
00:34:48.044 --> 00:34:50.546
<i>But I will not let that happen.</i>

535
00:34:50.630 --> 00:34:53.966
<i>I will not die</i>
<i>at the hands of mere spirits.</i>

536
00:34:54.467 --> 00:34:56.135
Night will soon fall.

537
00:34:56.219 --> 00:34:57.845
Court ladies are not to sleep tonight.

538
00:34:57.929 --> 00:35:01.474
They will all protect me
until daylight hours come!

539
00:35:02.558 --> 00:35:05.520
[Gu-cheon] So. for 30 years.
the pond spirit

540
00:35:05.603 --> 00:35:08.356
has been killing the princes
in the East Palace.

541
00:35:09.107 --> 00:35:12.235
And the court ladies wrote
that the princes were dying

542
00:35:12.318 --> 00:35:13.986
because of the Queen Dowager?

543
00:35:14.070 --> 00:35:15.571
It was not the court ladies' doing.

544
00:35:16.239 --> 00:35:18.074
They were falsely accused
and put to death.

545
00:35:19.575 --> 00:35:23.246
What is certain is that the pond spirit
is connected to the Queen Dowager.

546
00:35:25.164 --> 00:35:26.541
Still. thanks to your ability.

547
00:35:26.624 --> 00:35:29.252
I was able to learn why the court ladies
became won-gwi.

548
00:35:30.837 --> 00:35:32.505
I could not have done it alone.

549
00:35:33.673 --> 00:35:34.757
You did good work.

550
00:35:37.385 --> 00:35:38.553
You are the first person

551
00:35:39.595 --> 00:35:42.265
to say this strange ability
of mine was helpful.

552
00:35:42.348 --> 00:35:43.558
Is that so?

553
00:35:43.641 --> 00:35:45.184
I assumed His Majesty sent you to me

554
00:35:45.268 --> 00:35:46.978
because your ability
was a thing he valued.

555
00:35:47.061 --> 00:35:50.189
I must have proved to be of use
in helping with spirits.

556
00:35:55.611 --> 00:35:57.613
Are you in bad standing with your father?

557
00:35:57.697 --> 00:35:59.448
[unsettling music playing]

558
00:35:59.532 --> 00:36:00.992
[loud clattering]

559
00:36:01.576 --> 00:36:03.369
[King] Hold your wretched tongue.

560
00:36:03.452 --> 00:36:06.706
You must not tell me
that you can hear such atrocious things.

561
00:36:06.789 --> 00:36:09.125
Not any child who bears my blood.

562
00:36:09.834 --> 00:36:12.295
Unless you wish
to bring disgrace to our name.

563
00:36:14.172 --> 00:36:19.385
To hear such strange things would indeed
be a disgrace for the royal house.

564
00:36:23.139 --> 00:36:24.015
Sounds good to me.

565
00:36:27.310 --> 00:36:28.728
What do you mean by that?

566
00:36:30.354 --> 00:36:33.774
It's just that
since we both dislike the King.

567
00:36:33.858 --> 00:36:36.027
it makes it feel almost like
we are on the same side.

568
00:36:39.155 --> 00:36:40.364
Even so.

569
00:36:42.033 --> 00:36:46.454
when I heard those voices yelling
to be let out. I should've helped them.

570
00:36:47.955 --> 00:36:51.083
If only I had broken the jars
that their souls were imprisoned in.

571
00:36:51.167 --> 00:36:53.920
What could a mere child
have done to help them?

572
00:36:54.003 --> 00:36:56.714
Bearing such a strange gift
would've been hard enough.

573
00:36:57.757 --> 00:36:59.967
Don't carry that pointless guilt with you.

574
00:37:01.594 --> 00:37:03.596
[poignant music playing]

575
00:37:05.223 --> 00:37:09.143
I. too. was feared and pointed at
by others.

576
00:37:10.603 --> 00:37:12.980
You can simply ignore people like that.

577
00:37:17.401 --> 00:37:20.029
Just be mindful of them
and live your life so you don't end upâ€¦

578
00:37:20.112 --> 00:37:22.365
[imitates demon]
â€¦getting possessed like that.

579
00:37:29.413 --> 00:37:32.792
Now I understand why you're so unusual.

580
00:37:33.626 --> 00:37:34.460
Me?

581
00:37:35.836 --> 00:37:38.005
I'll make sure
they are correctly buried in the ground.

582
00:37:38.089 --> 00:37:40.007
-Whoa. whoa! Hey. hold on. Hold on.
-[music fades]

583
00:37:40.091 --> 00:37:43.135
I will grind these court ladies' bones
into powder.

584
00:37:44.178 --> 00:37:45.680
-[Saeng-gang] What?
-Hmm?

585
00:37:46.264 --> 00:37:47.807
[Saeng-gang] Ground into powder?

586
00:37:48.766 --> 00:37:50.393
No. you must not!

587
00:37:51.018 --> 00:37:52.812
Are you trying
to shame the dead once again?

588
00:37:52.895 --> 00:37:54.814
Oh. for crying out loud.

589
00:37:54.897 --> 00:37:57.400
It's a pain having to explain this
every time.

590
00:37:57.483 --> 00:38:01.153
A won-gwi is a spirit that cannot just
simply pass on to the afterlife

591
00:38:01.237 --> 00:38:03.155
because its resentment
is weighing it down.

592
00:38:03.906 --> 00:38:06.784
So if you use things
to help it remember who it once was.

593
00:38:06.867 --> 00:38:08.744
you can dissolve that resentmentâ€¦

594
00:38:10.788 --> 00:38:12.665
and send it to the afterlife.

595
00:38:13.416 --> 00:38:16.043
But then their souls
do not disappear. right?

596
00:38:16.127 --> 00:38:17.378
They are pitiful spirits.

597
00:38:17.461 --> 00:38:18.337
Hey.

598
00:38:18.421 --> 00:38:22.717
Pitiful or not. they are harming
innocent people around the palace now.

599
00:38:22.800 --> 00:38:24.302
[sighs] There's no time to explain.

600
00:38:24.385 --> 00:38:28.097
What do you mean "there's no time"?
Are you saying that others will appear?

601
00:38:31.267 --> 00:38:34.312
They're probably already
under the Queen Dowager's nose.

602
00:38:34.395 --> 00:38:37.273
-[unsettling music playing]
-[Queen reciting shaman chant]

603
00:38:44.780 --> 00:38:46.782
[chanting continues]

604
00:38:50.494 --> 00:38:53.039
[music intensifies]

605
00:38:53.122 --> 00:38:55.124
[music subsides]

606
00:39:01.339 --> 00:39:03.007
[Queen] Who is there?

607
00:39:04.050 --> 00:39:06.552
Bring me a candle at once.

608
00:39:15.269 --> 00:39:16.979
[agonized screaming]

609
00:39:18.731 --> 00:39:20.024
-[gasps]
-[metallic clank]

610
00:39:20.107 --> 00:39:22.109
[tense music playing]

611
00:39:31.410 --> 00:39:34.580
[Gu-cheon] <i>You will take this bone powder</i>
<i>and go to the Buddhist temple</i>

612
00:39:34.663 --> 00:39:36.499
<i>where the Queen Dowager is.</i>

613
00:39:37.917 --> 00:39:41.337
<i>I will go into the World of Gwi</i>
<i>and confront them.</i>

614
00:39:44.673 --> 00:39:47.093
<i>They will be with the Queen Dowager.</i>

615
00:39:49.929 --> 00:39:51.931
[spectral hissing]

616
00:39:57.728 --> 00:40:00.981
[shaman chanting. gasps]

617
00:40:01.065 --> 00:40:03.359
[spectral hissing]

618
00:40:03.442 --> 00:40:06.070
[crackling]

619
00:40:08.447 --> 00:40:09.990
[high-pitched tone]

620
00:40:10.699 --> 00:40:13.160
-[Gu-cheon exhales]
-[spectral hissing]

621
00:40:13.244 --> 00:40:14.328
[epic music playing]

622
00:40:14.412 --> 00:40:16.247
I am very sorry.

623
00:40:17.331 --> 00:40:19.458
-[Gu-cheon grunting]
-[spectral screeching]

624
00:40:21.419 --> 00:40:24.004
-[grunting]
-[spectral screeching]

625
00:40:25.506 --> 00:40:27.508
[sizzling]

626
00:40:31.470 --> 00:40:33.597
[spectral screeching]

627
00:40:35.558 --> 00:40:37.059
[grunting]

628
00:40:39.895 --> 00:40:40.771
[pants]

629
00:40:40.855 --> 00:40:42.690
[sizzling]

630
00:40:47.486 --> 00:40:50.448
[Gu-cheon] <i>As you said.</i>
<i>they are innocent won-gwi.</i>

631
00:40:50.531 --> 00:40:52.533
[spectral screeching]

632
00:40:53.325 --> 00:40:56.954
[Gu-cheon] <i>To set them free.</i>
<i>we must get rid of the mass of resentment.</i>

633
00:40:58.956 --> 00:41:01.500
<i>You must begin when I ring the bell.</i>

634
00:41:03.294 --> 00:41:05.880
-[spectral screeching]
-[grunting]

635
00:41:08.757 --> 00:41:09.967
[grunting echoes]

636
00:41:14.597 --> 00:41:16.223
[spectral screaming]

637
00:41:23.814 --> 00:41:25.566
[spectral screeching]

638
00:41:25.649 --> 00:41:27.902
[bell jingling]

639
00:41:27.985 --> 00:41:30.154
[Gu-cheon grunting]

640
00:41:30.237 --> 00:41:31.864
[jingling echoes]

641
00:41:34.950 --> 00:41:35.868
[grunts]

642
00:41:37.870 --> 00:41:38.954
[Gu-cheon grunts]

643
00:41:46.295 --> 00:41:48.255
[spectral screaming]

644
00:41:48.923 --> 00:41:50.508
[epic dramatic music playing]

645
00:41:50.591 --> 00:41:51.884
[screams]

646
00:41:51.967 --> 00:41:55.763
[screaming echoes]

647
00:41:57.473 --> 00:41:59.642
-[Gu-cheon grunts]
-[spectral screaming]

648
00:42:00.935 --> 00:42:02.019
[bell jingling]

649
00:42:04.063 --> 00:42:05.689
-[shrieks]
-[Gu-cheon grunts]

650
00:42:07.816 --> 00:42:10.277
[bell jingling]

651
00:42:10.361 --> 00:42:12.404
[music intensifies]

652
00:42:12.488 --> 00:42:13.322
[grunts]

653
00:42:19.537 --> 00:42:21.372
[music swells]

654
00:42:24.291 --> 00:42:26.544
[frantic music playing]

655
00:42:26.627 --> 00:42:28.504
[spectral howling]

656
00:42:28.587 --> 00:42:30.589
[Gu-cheon grunting]

657
00:42:34.301 --> 00:42:36.303
[music swells]

658
00:42:36.387 --> 00:42:38.389
-[music subsides]
-[breathing echoes]

659
00:42:40.891 --> 00:42:43.644
[spectral screaming]

660
00:42:43.727 --> 00:42:48.524
[screams frantically]

661
00:42:57.533 --> 00:42:59.743
[Gu-cheon] <i>So this is</i>
<i>the only way in the end?</i>

662
00:42:59.827 --> 00:43:02.121
[screaming continues]

663
00:43:03.747 --> 00:43:05.624
[Gu-cheon] <i>I am as good as dead.</i>

664
00:43:06.208 --> 00:43:07.042
[groans]

665
00:43:08.377 --> 00:43:11.046
-[spectral scream]
-[grunts]

666
00:43:11.755 --> 00:43:14.216
-[grunting continues]
-[screaming continues]

667
00:43:32.860 --> 00:43:36.614
-[bell jingling]
-Hurry. Saeng-gang! Do it now!

668
00:43:36.697 --> 00:43:38.574
[frantic music continues]

669
00:43:38.657 --> 00:43:40.534
[grunting echoes]

670
00:43:41.869 --> 00:43:43.871
[music subsides]

671
00:43:48.542 --> 00:43:52.046
[spectral screeching]

672
00:44:06.685 --> 00:44:08.020
[Gu-cheon pants]

673
00:44:14.485 --> 00:44:16.111
[Gu-cheon] <i>Let go of your grievancesâ€¦</i>

674
00:44:18.739 --> 00:44:20.908
<i>and lay your anger to rest.</i>

675
00:44:23.619 --> 00:44:26.205
<i>Now you can all find your peace.</i>

676
00:44:26.830 --> 00:44:27.956
[pants]

677
00:44:28.540 --> 00:44:30.125
-[squelching]
-[groaning]

678
00:44:30.209 --> 00:44:32.670
[Gu-cheon] <i>I will guide you</i>
<i>to the afterlife.</i>

679
00:44:34.129 --> 00:44:35.464
<i>May you allâ€¦</i>

680
00:44:35.547 --> 00:44:37.549
[groaning]

681
00:44:38.926 --> 00:44:41.178
<i>â€¦be reborn in paradise.</i>

682
00:44:43.555 --> 00:44:45.140
[exhales]

683
00:44:49.353 --> 00:44:51.355
[uplifting epic music playing]

684
00:44:54.817 --> 00:44:56.819
[groaning]

685
00:45:02.616 --> 00:45:03.742
[blade rasps]

686
00:45:09.039 --> 00:45:11.875
[Queen] We are innocent.

687
00:45:11.959 --> 00:45:14.795
We are resentful.

688
00:45:14.878 --> 00:45:18.132
We are innocent.

689
00:45:19.633 --> 00:45:21.927
We are resentful.

690
00:45:22.511 --> 00:45:23.887
[music fades]

691
00:45:23.971 --> 00:45:26.682
We are innocent. [sobs]

692
00:45:26.765 --> 00:45:30.144
-What my mother and I had to endureâ€¦
-[Queen] We are resentful.

693
00:45:30.227 --> 00:45:32.146
I've not forgotten about it.

694
00:45:32.229 --> 00:45:34.773
We are innocent.

695
00:45:35.691 --> 00:45:38.402
We are resentful.

696
00:45:38.485 --> 00:45:40.320
What are you so resentful about?

697
00:45:41.780 --> 00:45:43.782
[breathing shakily]

698
00:45:46.618 --> 00:45:47.703
Weâ€¦

699
00:45:49.413 --> 00:45:53.125
We were only guilty of being in that place
and put to death.

700
00:45:53.208 --> 00:45:54.084
[Saeng-gang] Who?

701
00:45:55.002 --> 00:45:56.628
Who is trying to speak?

702
00:45:57.129 --> 00:45:59.381
[stirring ethereal music playing]

703
00:45:59.465 --> 00:46:02.426
When she died.
the Most Favored Lady of the Courtâ€¦

704
00:46:02.509 --> 00:46:04.553
Uttered the curseâ€¦

705
00:46:06.096 --> 00:46:07.139
[sighs]

706
00:46:09.975 --> 00:46:14.229
From this day on. no royal blood
shall flow within these walls.

707
00:46:14.313 --> 00:46:17.399
You insolent wench!
How dare you speak in that manner!

708
00:46:17.483 --> 00:46:20.068
When I die and become a spirit.

709
00:46:20.736 --> 00:46:23.530
I will come back
to sever the royal bloodline.

710
00:46:24.239 --> 00:46:29.161
I will wipe out the royal bloodline
and dry out the seed of the East Palace!

711
00:46:29.244 --> 00:46:31.121
[screams. gasps]

712
00:46:31.205 --> 00:46:32.873
[Jang] What are you waiting for? Stop her!

713
00:46:32.956 --> 00:46:34.291
[women gasp]

714
00:46:39.755 --> 00:46:41.965
[women gasp. scream]

715
00:46:43.175 --> 00:46:47.137
[Queen] <i>"No royal blood shall flow</i>
<i>within this palace."</i>

716
00:46:47.888 --> 00:46:50.933
<i>"I will dry out the seed</i>
<i>of the East Palace."</i>

717
00:46:51.934 --> 00:46:55.896
<i>"The serpent's shed skin</i>
<i>killed the dragon's child."</i>

718
00:46:56.396 --> 00:46:58.273
<i>She killed us because we heard</i>

719
00:46:58.357 --> 00:47:00.984
<i>the Most Favored Lady</i>
<i>of the Court's curse.</i>

720
00:47:01.985 --> 00:47:07.533
Under the pretense
of the writing on the wallâ€¦

721
00:47:07.616 --> 00:47:09.618
[Queen gasps. groans]

722
00:47:12.037 --> 00:47:14.790
[Saeng-gang] The curse by
The Most Favored Lady of the Court?

723
00:47:15.833 --> 00:47:17.209
[Queen gasping]

724
00:47:17.960 --> 00:47:20.212
[Saeng-gang] Does that mean
the pond spirit's true identity

725
00:47:20.295 --> 00:47:22.130
is the Most Favored Lady of the Court?

726
00:47:24.675 --> 00:47:27.386
[labored] We are innocent.

727
00:47:27.469 --> 00:47:29.304
[gasping]

728
00:47:29.888 --> 00:47:32.850
While we were in there.
being burned alive.

729
00:47:33.600 --> 00:47:37.521
why did you stand by
and do nothing to save us?

730
00:47:37.604 --> 00:47:39.356
[tense music playing]

731
00:47:39.439 --> 00:47:43.443
[Gu-cheon] <i>Those who commit sins</i>
<i>are bound to be punished eventually.</i>

732
00:47:46.697 --> 00:47:49.616
<i>You do not need to take a life</i>
<i>with your own hands.</i>

733
00:47:52.286 --> 00:47:53.662
[music fades]

734
00:47:53.745 --> 00:47:55.747
{\an8}[hard rock music playing]

735
00:50:38.744 --> 00:50:40.746
[music fades]
